Condensers EC-1 and EC-2 condense the high pressure ammonia vapor back to a high pressure liquid. The condensing process is facilitated by water that is sprayed on the condenser coils and air drawn over the coils by the condenser fans. The resulting high pressure ammonia liquid drains back to the High Pressure Receiver to be re-used in the refrigeration process.

The system is also equipped with an Auto Purger which removes non-condensables in the system (air and water).

Accidental Release Prevention Program
Trinity Frozen Foods has developed an accidental release prevention program for compliance with the EPA RMP regulation.  The program includes but is not limited to the following elements:
•	Process safety information regarding the hazards of ammonia, and operating and technical specifications for the refrigeration system and the associated equipment;
•	Written procedures for operating and maintaining the refrigeration system;
•	Training for personnel involved with system operations and maintenance;
•	Written procedures for safely introducing modifications to the process;
•	Investigating releases of ammonia and near miss incidents and implementing measures to prevent recurrence; 
•	Written procedures for conducting hot work on or near the process;
•	Contractor management policies to ensure contract employee safety while on facility premises;
•	Audit procedures for ensuring that the programs are being implemented in accordance with the regulations; and
•	Employee involvement in program development and implementation.

